      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HECTOR DARCY (6) turned in a plain performance last time when fifth at this track over 600m behind Viking Ruler (35.44) in a R/A FIN. Was in the money the start prior. Tough to beat if on-song. MY MATE LEO (1) has some solid form under his belt and proved too classy last time to win by 3.5 lengths at this track in a handy 30.24 beating Paw Bennett. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. One of main contenders. RADAR O'REILLY (2) is a progressive type who recorded his 6th career win last time out (29.72) at Sandown. Form here sound including two wins. Has a solid record from this box including two wins and a minor placing. Flying at the moment and expecting another big run. AUNTY FAYE (3) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.",
